The man, who was employed at the ANC’s Luthuli House headquarters, is accused of being involved in a cash-in-transit heist in Soweto Errol Velile Present was nabbed by a multi-disciplinary team for allegedly being involved in a cash-in-transit heist in Soweto, along with three accomplices. During his arrest police, also recovered four vehicles believed to have been hijacked. He has since appeared in court and is expected to apply for bail along with three other suspects at the end of this month. National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) and the Hawks have said more charges could be added to the case. Present’s alleged involvement in the crime surfaced on Wednesday morning when City of Joburg Mayor Herman Mashaba alleged in a statement that one of the men involved in a cash-in-transit heist was an ANC employee. READ MORE: Joburg Mayor says cash-in-transit robbery suspect works for ANC The man is allegedly embroiled in several heinous crimes. Police Minister Bheki Cele has revealed that the former ANC employee has been linked to other three heists. He said the man has escaped court processes in cases he was linked to before. Talking to Bongani Bingwa on Talk Radio 702 on Thursday morning, Cele said they have established that he was linked to another heist. “The arrest of Errol Velile Present is the arrest of just another criminal. What we have established is that Velile is linked to another cash heist [that happened] before this, other cases and drunken driving,” he said. READ MORE: How to stay safe if you witness a cash-in-transit heist Gauteng NPA spokesperson Phindi Mjonondwane told The Star that more charges, including the possession of stolen property, could be added to the charges Present faced once investigators had concluded their investigation.